Basically what happened is, as team 10034, we set our team number to roborio, and the ip becomes 10.10.3.95, instead of 10.100.34.2, and it seems like we cannot change the roborio ip, since we will not be able to connect or ping new ip 10.100.34.2. Somehow when we try to set 1003 as our temporary number for roborio, it worked well and the ip is correct 10.10.3.2.

Here we have 2 question. The first one is how can we adjust our ip to 10.100.34.2, and the second is if we can use 10.10.3.x ip IN OFFICIAL PLAYS since there team 1003 is no longer active, according to the blue alliance.

We appreciate your help!

By default the roboRIO get’s a DHCP IP address of 10.TE.AM.2 (or in your case 10.TTE.AM.2) from the radio, the roboRIO imaging tool does not set an IP address.

Are you able to connect to your roboRIO via USB and set a static IP?

FIRST Robotics Competition Documentation

roboRIO Network Troubleshooting

The roboRIO and FRC ® tools use dynamic IP addresses ( DHCP) for network connectivity. This article describes steps for troubleshooting networking connectivity between your PC and your roboRIO Ping...
